        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/13/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 10:24:23</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=1525"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1525')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=27054&TOPIC_ID=2984&FORUM_ID=7&CAT_ID=2&Forum_Title=Daily+Discussion&Topic_Title=Enforcing+of+Verant%27s+EBay+policies&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I have one major reason for being against Ebay sales. It's that this game is intended as a fantasy world, where I can go and be who I want to be. Where I can start on equal ground with a few thousand other people and hope to excel based purely on my talent and skill. The amount of time I invest should return reasonably compared to another player, based directly on how much smarter and able I am than he. </P><P>In the real world, I have to bend to the will of people who have excesses of money. I have to work for them, vote for them, compete against thier higher quality education, etc. Thier station in life has put them at an advantage over me. Not saying that this is a hurdle that cannot be over-come, or that it's unfair or anything else. This is purely reality. People born to money, or who have acquired money have advantage in our world. My point is, I don't want to pay to go to a fantasy world, to compete purely on merit, and have the same people with money have an advantage over me there as well. I don't really care where thier money comes from, and it's irrelevant. The fact is, I want to be able to be able to know I have the status in the fantasy world over another becuase I earned it. I don't want to look over and see Little Johnny, who is 14 and gets a $750 a month allowance at level 20 in a full suit of Cobalt with his first character. He didn't earn it. Period. He has gained something that would take me months of enormous effort to gain, purely because Mommy and Daddy spoil him. His parents bankroll has belittled my efforts, and that is not why I log into a fantasy world.</P><P>The same theory holds true for people who work a lot, and spend lots of time with family. If they cannot, or will not invest the same effort in a fantasy world that I have, there is no reason that they should easily attain something in it that I cannot easily attain. It defeats the purpose of being in a fantasy world to escape reality. In these cases reality interferes with the level of accomplishment for the player who would earn on merit, and not buy their way to power.</P><P>I don't care how many FBSS's get destroyed. I don't care how many hours of work someone put into a character are deleted along with that character. What I do care about is knowing that there is a destinct possiblity that the level 56 druid that just stole the AC spawn from me was bought not more than 2 weeks earlier by a first time player, and that he has used his real-world influence of cash to interfere with my hard-fought accomplishments in this fantasy world. My effort earned me the right to be at that place at that time. He bought his right to be there and destroy the possible fruits of my effort. </P><P>Last, I'm tired of grouping with the idiots that bought all thier equipment, which allowed them to advance a bit quickly. I grouped with a level 47 Druid a week or so ago, that was castin Harmony in the middle of the fight, on mobs that were agro already, because " they would'nt hit has hard if they were calmer ". Tell me this person actually leveled up to 47 on merit. Another guy, a 53 warrior in EC, asked in ooc if Bronze was better than crafted. Jesus, get these people out of the way. Let people who play the game from the start, and understand the game, get to the levels that are meant for people with knowledge and talent.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

