        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">One last point: Someone mentioned that this is entertainment. They asked why they shouldnt be able to buy a ticket to a movie or a concert. Do you think it would be fair for you to buy the same ticket I buy to a movie, and I slip the guy at the door an extra ten, he comes to you and tells you to get out of my seat and tells you to go sit in the back? How about both of us paying the same amount for a concert ticket, and I get to sit up front becuase I gave the security gaurds $100 and you get to sit right behind a pole? Is this justifiable? No. It's BS. In both cases I would be crippling you're chosen form of entertainment strickly becuase I have extra bucks to blow. May have to be the case in the real world, but all be damned if I want to pay for it in a fantasy world as well. </P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
