        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">To be honest I agree with all of you.</P><P>I can see how if someone wants to put up money to save them time it would be ok.  I can also understand how someone that has played and played can hate it when they ding 51 and run into some guy that just paid 500 dollars for the same class and race and is now one day into the game with a level 52 char.  I actualy didnt really like eq to begin with.  I had a large group of friends play and talk about it and I have seen it totally creap into there lives but then a friend of mine said that he wanted to quit the game but if he had it he would play so he gave me the game and when I started he had never deleted any char.  His highest was a 15th level cleric.  I had no idea how to play the class.  I had many people wanting me to group with them but I told them that I wouln't because of my lack of actual exp.  If you are one of those people that do buy char or what not I urge you to start another char of that race and type and begin to learn the newances of the game I mean you dont want to be in seb one day shouting about how you wish someone would show you how to make a button then no one would group with you fearing your newbieness , I guess thats a word, would get them killed.  I also had the thought that if I ever get to level 60 and get tired of this game and do sell my account it would be kind of neat to actually see if you can become kos in every town.  So that someone wants to cheat and buy into it thinking that they are the bad azzes thats another way to know if someone has bought there char most level 55 plus people have a mature demenure most anyway because we all know that being cocky can get you killed faster than pulling while oom and if you dont know what oom is please dont run to skyshrine the first second that you try out your new 60th uber char for only 1999.95 not sold in stores:)  But that is just my 2cp.</P><P>Garmwer</P><P> <a href="#top">